The item "Earthshatter Hauberk" (43767) is included in the default item cache, but according to the armory does not exist in game.  Wowhead indicates it may have been a placeholder for the Heroes' Earthshatter Hauberk (39592) which does exist and is identical other than the name.
WorkItem.Summary: [Items] Earthshatter Hauberk should not be in the item cache

Comments.Message: Any time load upgrades from wowhead/armoury is selected some of the placeholders get loaded into the item cache. Simply select the item then select and delete the offending item. No more worries.

Other items to add to this list:

"Dreamwalker Shoulderpads" (43758)
"Dreamwalker Raiments" (43822)
"Dreamwalker Handgrips" (43751)

They where replaced with the "Heroes'" set.

@Brituck: I'm not talking about "load upgrades", which I never use, but about the default item cache.  Deleting items that don't exist every time a new version comes along is a pain.

@MTRazeR: thanks, I had noticed those ones too but lost the post-it note ;-)

To clarify, these are coming from the armory, which has bad items on it and suggests them as upgrades.  In other words, not a Rawr bug.

I think it could be useful to add a 'blacklist' type feature to Rawr however, since these will keep re-appearing.
